qas.question: By 2011, how many people were affected by asthma?

answers.text: 235–330 million people worldwide are affected by asthma

qas.question: How many people die per year from asthma?
What countries is asthma more commonly seen?

answers.text: It is more common in developed than developing countries

qas.question: Why are different countries effected differently?

answers.text: The reason for these differences is not well known

How many people died in 2011 in Europe from asthma?
What percentage of people in developing countries are affluent?
What percentage of people in Eastern Europe are affluent?
Is it known why developing countries are economically disadvantaged?
